# 🚀 DevPulse: Developer Productivity & Time Tracker SaaS

DevPulse is an all-in-one SaaS platform designed for developers to automatically track their coding hours, analyze repository metrics, and visualize their productivity patterns through an interactive dashboard and a dedicated VS Code extension.

---

## ✨ Features

* **⚡ Real-Time Tracking:** VS Code Extension securely streams heartbeat signals to record your active coding intervals.
* **📊 GitHub Integration:** Fetches and visualizes repository commit histories, branches, and collaboration metrics via GitHub OAuth.
* **🧩 Interactive Dashboard:** Beautiful frontend analytics build with React and Vite to view your daily, weekly, and monthly productivity charts.
* **📦 Modern DevOps Architecture:** Fully containerized environment powered by Docker and automated test workflows via GitHub Actions.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Frontend & Extension
* **Framework:** React (Vite)
* **Language:** TypeScript / JavaScript
* **Styling:** TailwindCSS
* **IDE Integration:** VS Code Extension API

### Backend & Database
* **Framework:** FastAPI (Python 3.10)
* **Database:** PostgreSQL 15
* **ORM:** SQLAlchemy / Alembic

### DevOps & CI/CD
* **Containerization:** Docker & Docker Compose
* **Automation:** GitHub Actions (CI/CD Pipeline)

---

## 🚀 Getting Started (Local Development)

### Prerequisites
Make sure you have **Docker Desktop** and **Git** installed on your system.

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/devpulse.git](https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/devpulse.git)
cd devpulse
2. Configure Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory and insert your GitHub OAuth credentials:

Code snippet
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret
3. Spin up the Containers
Run the following magic command to build and launch the database, backend, and frontend simultaneously:

Bash
docker compose up --build
4. Access the Applications
Once the build is complete, you can access the services at:

Frontend Dashboard: http://localhost:5173

Backend API (Swagger Docs): http://localhost:8001/docs

PostgreSQL Database Port: 5435 (Internal container port: 5432)

🔒 Production & CI/CD
This project includes a fully automated GitHub Actions Pipeline (.github/workflows/deploy.yml). On every push or pull request to the main branch, the pipeline automatically:

Provisions an isolated PostgreSQL test instance.

Installs and tests Python and Node.js dependencies.

Builds and verifies Docker production images.


